text: Hey guys sorry I wasn't responsive yesterday. I agree we really need to focus on the functionality of the app first and foremost. Judging from some of the examples they gave us, it really needs to be something simple like an expense tracker, library manager, or event log. They keep saying a lot of groups do "recipe managers" but I think it's possible and good for us to do something a little more creative and complex. I'll post a link to the some of the samples they gave us. I'm really ok with working on any project as long as its not out of the scope of the assignment guidelines. The fitness app is fine but <@U0574FFA3L5> what did you mean by "quality of life feature"? I think they're expecting something very similar to the functionality to Carrie's art gallery app she taught us with. So some things I could see working for a fitness app would be: "Create workout"- user can set type i.e. "cardio" "strength" "therapy" and add details to exercises in that workout. "Personal Records"- user can make a card when they hit a PR wether with weights, running distance, body weight. "Goals"- user can set goals and set a time frame, maybe include a comment section to describe the smaller steps to that goal. I agree the BMI is outdated and there is an awesome episode of the "Maintenance Phase" podcast about it. The sports team idea I think relies on and centers too much around the api and I believe would get too complicated too quickly. However I could see a project where a user can set up a personal page that shows: They're favorite teams, games they've attended, favorite players, and a "Dream Team" creator for every sport. We really need to finish the project proposal sheet ASAP and would encourage all communication center on it until it's completed.

text:
Front End Work
Create an Account
	-Design and implement user registration and login forms.
	-Develop user interfaces for account creation and authentication.
	-Use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create a seamless and user-friendly experience.

Create Workout Plans
	-Design a user interface for creating new workout plans.
	-Implement forms for users to input details such as workout name, exercises, sets, 	 	reps, etc.
	-Utilize JavaScript to handle form validation and improve user interaction.

Read Workout Plans
	-Develop a user interface to display a list of workout plans.
	-Fetch workout plans from the server asynchronously.
	-Design a clean and intuitive layout for users to view their existing workout 			plans.

Update Workout Plans
	-Create interfaces for users to edit existing workout plans.
	-Implement forms with pre-filled data for easy modification.
	-Use JavaScript to handle the update requests and provide real-time feedback.

Delete Workout Plans
	-Design confirmation dialogs or modal windows for users to confirm deletion.
	-Implement functionality to send delete requests to the server.

Search for Individual Exercises
	-Develop a search bar or interface to allow users to search for individual 			exercises.
	-Dynamically display search results.

Example Workouts Based on Search Parameters
	-Implement a feature to filter and display example workouts based on search 			parameters.
	-Utilize JavaScript to dynamically update the content based on user input.

Back-End Work
User Authentication:
	-Develop server-side logic for user registration and login.
	-Implement authentication middleware to secure routes.

Workout Plans Management
	-Design and create a database schema to store workout plans.
	-Implement server-side logic to handle the creation, retrieval, updating, and 			deletion of workout plans.
	-Create API endpoints for CRUD operations on workout plans.

Exercise Database
	-Set up a database to store information about individual exercises.
	-Implement API endpoints to search for exercises based on user input.

Example Workouts Generation
	-Implement logic to generate example workouts based on specified parameters.
	-Utilize the exercise database to create diverse and effective workout examples.

Security
	-Implement security measures to protect user data and prevent unauthorized access.
	-Validate and sanitize user inputs on the server side to prevent potential security 		vulnerabilities.
